node.text:
A new biotechnology company is aiming to genetically resurrect the Woolly Mammoth by 2027👀‼️ 

According to Fox News, Colossal, which launched on Monday, has received $15 million in initial funding for the project. the company discussed the issue of extinction and its goal to "develop a de-extinction library of animals as well as housing genetic DNA/embryos from endangered animals.

"This process will slow the long-term impacts of human induced loss of biodiversity and give threatened species a buffer against outright extinction as numbers dwindle," the site read.➡️Follow @steez for more ‼️
